the scheme of allegorical wall and ceiling decorations of the hall depicts the protestant succession of english monarchs from william and mary to george i.   on 28 june 1715 thornhill was awarded the commission to decorate the dome of st paul 's cathedral by " a whig , low - church dominated committee inspired by a moral anglican nationalism " .

dome , sweet dome : the frescoes that decorate the interior of the dome of this london cathedral are by sir james thornhill

